name: Parmesan Fish Sticks with Malt Vinegar Dipping Sauce
author: Skif2206
summary: This is an easy-to-make, healthier version of your classic, delicious fish stick. Kids love them and they're fast and easy to make.
ingredients: salt and ground black pepper to taste
4 (6 ounce) halibut fillets, cut into 3x1/2-inch strips
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C)
Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil
Whisk flour, salt, and pepper together in a shallow bowl
Beat eggs in a separate bowl until frothy, about 30 seconds
Combine panko bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, basil, and oregano in a third shallow bowl
Dredge fish through the flour mixture until evenly coated, shaking off excess flour
Dip fish into egg, allowing excess egg to drip into bowl
Press fish into the panko mixture until evenly coated
Arrange coated fish on the prepared baking sheet
Cook in the preheated oven until fish sticks are golden brown and flake easily with a fork, about 15 minutes
Mix ketchup, mayonnaise, and malt vinegar together in a bowl and serve alongside fish sticks
